Title:
CrystalForge (AdaptixC2 agent extender with Crystal Palace UDRL pipeline)

Type:
GitHub Tool

Short Summary (4–8 sentences max):
CrystalForge is a custom AdaptixC2 agent/extender that modifies the default beacon build pipeline to integrate Crystal Palace’s UDRL (User-Defined Reflective Loader) workflow. It aims to make it easier to generate Adaptix payloads that are post-processed through Crystal Palace using selectable `.spec` files, enabling custom loader techniques for evasion and experimentation. The tool supports generating DLL and shellcode outputs, where shellcode is produced by taking an intermediate DLL and linking/transforming it via Crystal Palace according to the chosen spec. It preserves the standard Adaptix beacon feature set and multi-transport support while adding a flexible loader integration layer. Limitations noted include lack of EXE/service outputs and incomplete coverage for dynamically resolved APIs (focus is on IAT-resolved functions). It’s primarily useful for red teams, offensive security researchers, and malware tradecraft developers working on loader customization and C2 payload generation workflows.

Technical Focus:
- AdaptixC2 extender/agent plugin architecture
- Crystal Palace UDRL pipeline and `.spec`-driven loader selection
- DLL-to-shellcode transformation via intermediate DLL processing
- Windows reflective loading / PE loader concepts
- API hooking constraints (IAT vs dynamically resolved APIs)
- Loader development workflow (precompiled external loader components)

Use Cases:
- Integrate custom Crystal Palace loaders into AdaptixC2 payload generation
- Produce shellcode variants from a standard beacon DLL using different UDRL specs
- Rapidly test/iterate loader techniques (evasion-focused) within a C2 workflow
- Standardize operator workflow for selecting loader specs during build time
- Research and prototype reflective loader/PE loading tradecraft

Keywords:
AdaptixC2, CrystalForge, Crystal Palace, UDRL, reflective loader, PE loader, shellcode generation, DLL payload, beacon, C2 agent, spec file, loader pipeline, IAT hooking, Windows internals, MinGW, C, C++, Go, stack spoofing, Crystal-Kit